hf_response.name: MISELECT_VALUE_ACCESS_TYPE
hf_response.description: The VALUE field is read‑write as specified by the Type entry.

hf_response.name: MISELECT_VALUE_RESET_VALUE
hf_response.description: If no extensions use the indirect register window, the register reads as zero.
hf_response.spec_quote: The `miselect` register may be read-only zero if there are no extensions implemented that utilize it.

hf_response.name: MISELECT_VALUE_WARL_LEGAL_VALUES
hf_response.description: Values whose most‑significant bit is clear and that are allocated to standard extensions are legal; custom values (MSB set) are legal only if the implementation supports them.
hf_response.spec_quote: Values of `miselect` with the most-significant bit clear are designated only for standard use and are reserved until allocated to a standard architecture extension.

hf_response.name: MISELECT_VALUE_WARL_ILLEGAL_VALUES
hf_response.description: Values that are not allocated to any standard extension and custom values when the implementation does not support them are illegal.
hf_response.spec_quote: An implementation is not required to support any custom values for `miselect`.

hf_response.name: MISELECT_VALUE_WARL_MAPPING
hf_response.description: Writes of illegal values may be treated as UNDEFINED_LEGAL_DETERMINISTIC, allowing the implementation to choose a legal value.
hf_response.spec_quote: An implementation is not required to support any custom values for `miselect`.
